How can i concate the below firstName and lastName without + operator?

console.log("Full Name:", firstName + lastName);


Solutions:

✅ 1. Template literals (most modern & recommended):

    const firstName = "John";
    const lastName = "Doe";
    
    console.log(`Full Name: ${firstName} ${lastName}`);


✅ 2. String.concat() method:

      const firstName = "John";
      const lastName = "Doe";
      
      console.log("Full Name:", firstName.concat(" ", lastName));



✅ 3. Array + join():

    const firstName = "John";
    const lastName = "Doe";
    
    console.log("Full Name:", [firstName, lastName].join(" "));



✅ 4. Intl.ListFormat (cool trick, also handles localization):

    const firstName = "John";
    const lastName = "Doe";
    
    const formatter = new Intl.ListFormat("en", { style: "long", type: "conjunction" });
    console.log("Full Name:", formatter.format([firstName, lastName]));





⚡ The simplest and modern way is Template literals (`${firstName} ${lastName}`).



